title: Kellogg's Special K Protein Meal Bars, 12g Protein Snacks, Meal Replacement, Chocolatey Chip Cookie Dough, 19oz Box (12 Bars)
description: About this item    Deliciously portable protein meal bar made to fuel and fill you up without slowing you down    Satisfies taste buds with a chocolatey chip cookie dough flavored inside and a chocolatey coating outside    12g protein (23% daily value, 4.5g saturated fat per serving); 6g fiber (6g total fat per serving); Contains soy, milk, almond, peanut and wheat ingredients; May contain other tree nuts    Energizing, satisfying meal or snack for work, errands, pre workout and more; Stash in desk, car, and bag for when hunger strikes    Includes 1, 19-ounce box of 12 convenient, ready-to-eat meal bars; Individually wrapped for freshness and great taste

title: Kirkland Signature Protein bar energy variety pack,
reviews: {"author": "Pug Dog owner", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Awesome Bars!", "content": "Oh boy, where do I even begin with these Kirkland signature protein bars? Let me just say that my taste buds are doing the macarena right now!First off, the texture is just right. It's chewy but not too much, and it's not like those other protein bars that taste like you're biting into gravel. These bars are softer than a baby's bottom and they are packed with flavor.Speaking of flavors, have you tried the chocolate brownie one? I don't even know how they did it, but it tastes like a legit brownie. I'm convinced there are tiny little chocolate fairies working tirelessly in the Kirkland factory to make these bars extra delicious.And let's not forget about the peanut butter flavor. It's like eating a spoonful of creamy peanut butter, minus the weird looks from your coworkers. Trust me, I've been there.But the best part? These bars have a jaw-dropping 21 grams of protein. That's more than enough to power through a workout or just power nap on your couch, whichever you prefer.Overall, these Kirkland signature protein bars deserve all five stars and a standing ovation. I just hope they don't raise the price because I might have to sell my soul to pay for them.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2023", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Nicholas Harvey", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Kirkland Signature Protein bar", "content": "The bars are goo and satisfying. I would recommend them for the value and flavor. The only con if you want to call it that is they are sticky. They stick to the packaging and to your fingers.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 11, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Debbie J", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Best flavored Protein bars; no aftertaste", "content": "I just began using protein bars because of a low serum protein. There are plenty of brands to try and many have a rather distasteful aftertaste. Kirtland\u2019s is better than most, but their bar texture is not the easiest to eat: chewy, hard, mud and grainy! But the taste is much better with no aftertaste. My least favorite is their Chocolate chip cookie dough:  Quest makes a better bar in that category. However, Kirtland\u2019s are my first choice if I run out and are a decent price at Costco. The one thing that became a problem with protein bars in general was constipation.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 15, 2021", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "mary kate priest", "rating": "4.0 ", "title": "Good flavor/Numbers", "content": "A little chewy, but the numbers on them are good, beating out my usual, Pure Protein brand. These are lower in sugar. Definitely cheaper at Costco, but in a jam... shop out a cheap source on Amazon.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Cindy from MN", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "great flavor", "content": "these bars keep you full for four hours.  it takes six hours before you really know you are hungry.  great for diets and summer activity", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on July 13, 2023", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Xero Requiem", "rating": "1.0 ", "title": "Recommend staying away from both flavors for the slim per bar savings.", "content": "I bought these as a possible replacement to quest bars due to how many I eat(1-2 per day). The flavor varieties are limited to just these two, but the cost savings depending on where you buy your quest bars can be in the range of $0.60 to $1+ per bar.I tried both bars today. The brownie one is flat out horrible. 0/5 if I could. The flavor profile reminds me of cheap chocolate, and actually trying to eat the bar is essentially like chewing gum. After about chewing my first bite of the bar for about 30 seconds I spit it out and moved onto the next one.The chocolate cookie dough one is subpar at best. Might be worth a 1.5-2/5. I was actually able to chew and swallow my bite of this one, but rather than tasting like cookie dough, or even like a cookie dough imitation, which is what the somewhat okay quest bar version does for this flavor, it instead tastes like it is instead trying to mimic the flavor of something trying to mimic the flavor of cookie dough. So what you end up with is a worse version of the quest bar version of this flavor which is already only alright in its own right, and is one of their weakest bars in their lineup.In the end, someone at Kirkland decided it would be a good idea to take two of the worst quest bar flavors, and then make even cheaper versions of them, which in the end is reflected by the barely palatable taste of each. I wouldn't recommend anyone buying these. I'll try to see if someone I know likes them as maybe they wouldn't mind taking 18 free protein bars.In the end the only way these compare to the quest bars, is in their macro nutrient counts. In the end though, I signed up for 5 boxes of quest bars a month until I get a decent stock pile so I can take advantage of the 15% discount. That puts my price at $20-$21 per box or $1.75 per quest bar compared to ~$1.35 per bar for these. It is well worth the extra $0.40 per bar so I am not revolted by what I am eating and can actually enjoy the product I am paying for.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2017", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "HRPuckinfutz", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Doesn't Give Me Gas", "content": "These protein bars are the only ones that don't give me gas. If you are embarrassed about passing gas while doing sit-ups in the gym, these are the perfect protein bar. They taste good, too, except for the peanut butter ones. I love peanut butter, but those don't taste great.The price is inflated. It is cheaper to purchase these from Costco, but they don't ship overseas.I have had an issue on occasion where the inside plastic film of the wrapper separated from the foil and stuck to the bar. The first time this happened I didn't notice until I had eaten three quarters of the bar. Let's just say that the plastic film didn't pass well. A few other times that happened I simply peeled the plastic film from the bar.Buy these at COSTCO if you can and save yourself about $10 a box.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on May 2, 2020", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Liam Bennett", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Great low cost protein and fiber bar for hiking, golfing, and everyday life.", "content": "Perfect low cost source of protein and fiber. I have had trouble figuring out healthy, gluten free alternatives that don\u2019t make my stomach hurt and these work great. I really enjoy the cookie dough flavor, the REAL chocolate chips make them taste like cookies. I throw them everywhere from my everyday laptop bag to my golf bag. Love this product!!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2022", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Amazon Customer", "rating": "2.0 ", "title": null, "content": "This new recipe does not play well with my stomach!  I've heard the same from several people.  Beware.", "date": "Reviewed in Canada on March 7, 2019", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Heather Floyd", "rating": "1.0 ", "title": null, "content": "These bars taste quite good and the net carbs work out well.  However, be very aware that these will very likely give you intestinal upset, bloating and intestinal gas.  It is quite significant and if at work or at a social outing they would cause great distress.  If you google this concern, you will read about similar reviews and they chalk it up to the presence of inulin in the product?", "date": "Reviewed in Canada on June 8, 2019", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Hardy", "rating": "2.0 ", "title": null, "content": "I was super excited to try this. reviews: {"author": "Alex Raleigh", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Great snack for neurodivergent folks with gut/sensory issues!", "content": "I absolutely love this brand of applesauce packets. I've tried others, such as Motts, but I find them too sugary. This brand is the most natural tasting - only 3 ingredients (apples, apple puree, and lemon juice). Its not too sugary, but not bland. I find that the regular and cinimon flavors are best for me sugar wise. I am autistic, and have a lot of sensory issues re: food and food texture. This is my go to safe food. Its super easy to consume in the morning (when its the hardest for me to stomach food); I love throwing one in my purse for a snack later on. The texture is not as smooth as Motts - I like that it has more of the applesauce puree chunks (not actual chunks). Finally, it doesn't upset my stomach. The characters are great, including my top three favorites known as Saeyoung, Saeran, and Yoosung.But...what does that have to do with this product?I'll tell you.Saeyoung Choi, AKA 707, has a favorite snack that consists of Honey Butter Chips and Ph. D Pepper. Even better these look like the exact same brand, only the ones I recieved had the writing in English as pictured. I didn't think these were real until I decided to look them up on Amazon last week. The chips remind me of Lay's but not as thin and won't break at even the lightest touch like Lay's. The chips is a sweet buttery flavor with a hint of honey to it. title: Jack Link's Beef Jerky, Sweet & Hot, Spicy Meat Snack  9g of Protein & 80 Calories, Made with Premium Beef, No added MSG** or Nitrates/Nitrites, 5.85 oz
description: About this item    MADE WITH 100% BEEF : Our Sweet & Hot Beef Jerky is made of lean cuts of 100% premium beef. It's 96% fat free and has no added MSG and no added nitrates or nitrites.    GOOD SOURCE OF PROTEIN : Protein is an essential part of diets and Sweet & Hot Beef Jerky is a great way to get more. With 9g of protein and 80 calories per serving, it's a protein-packed meat snack that helps keep you satisfied when you need it most.    RESEALABLE SHARING SIZE :The jumbo 5.85 oz. sharing size bag is resealable and has about 6 servings in each bag. It's perfect for sharing with family and friends on a hunting trip or to stash in your secret spot and keep all to yourself.    FULL ON FLAVOR :It's the best of both worlds: heat and sweet. We marinate each strip of our Sweet & Hot Jerky with a blend of smoky sweet chili and black pepper. This combo builds while you're eating for heat perfectly balanced with a touch of sweet.    PERFECT EVERYDAY SNACK : How did ancient civilizations fuel themselves to cross oceans or win sword battles? Meat. If it worked for them, Jack Link's Beef Jerky can help you power thru a late day at work, tackle your honey-do list or fuel a workout.

Very expensive so will roast my own from now on.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 16, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "James C Young", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "These Use To Be My Favorite, But\u2026.", "content": "This use to be my favorite and my \u201cgo to\u201d pecan\u2019s for snacking on while watching TV or a mid-day snack before lunch or dinner. I decided to try a competitor and now the competitor has won me over. These are very good and always fresh. I have purchased these for years as a snack and I still love them. They are great and I can\u2019t say anything bad about them. The only thing that I have found is that occasionally I have gotten the bitter part in the pecan and it\u2019s not a bad taste, but for the price, I would think that you shouldn\u2019t get any of the bitter flavor from the pecan that is part of the shell that\u2019s soft and has a bitter taste to it. However, I would still recommend these for pecan lovers.Unfortunately for Planters, I decided to try the mammoth variety that their compilation Fisher has started marketing and they are very good at a lower price point than Planter\u2019s. I generally prefer the Planters Deluxe version because they are better quality and larger in size. They also cost more money, but you get what you pay for. One of the biggest drawbacks for the Fisher Brand is that my husband is on a low sodium diet and Planters has a few different salt free varieties of their snack sized containers of nuts. So, I\u2019ll never completely abandon the Planters brand, but my current favorite as far as salted pecans are the ones that Fisher has started selling.My husband is a 7th generation Texan and he is a huge pecan fan. His father had one tree that grew a variety of pecan called \u201cPodsednic\u201d which are the largest he says he has ever seen. They had several varieties on their land and they basically grew them for themselves and the community that he grew up in. He doesn\u2019t think the Fisher nuts are that variety, but he was impressed with the size of them. His father could graft trees and they always took without a problem. They had pecan trees that grew two or three different varieties of pecans. He even had a fruit tree he had done grafts on that grew plums and peaches. He won a Blue Ribbon for growing the smallest pecan in Texas. My husband tried his hand at grafting a few times and we had the help of a botanist that was a good friend and they never took. So I guess it\u2019s just something you can or cannot do. His father tried to teach him how to do grafting successfully and he still couldn\u2019t get them to take. We actually have unsalted pecans that we buy at the grocery store by Fisher and they are the only ones that he will buy for cooking. We generally drive out to the various growers and buy them directly from the grower\u2019s. However the last two cold winters, the first one a record breaking winter, and the drought has made the few growers that still have pecans for sale rather expensive. Unfortunately, some of the growers have lost  whole groves of trees and their main source of income. We still buy from local growers to keep them in business and they are extremely happy to see people enjoying their harvest. The pecan tree is the Texas state tree, and it\u2019s really hard to see the devastation that climate change has created for these growers. Many of them are multigenerational farms that have been around longer than anyone alive. It\u2019s heartbreaking to see how much has changed in the 26yrs that I\u2019ve lived in Texas.Not to get too political, but I personally think our Governor should have put a moratorium on home building several years ago. We don\u2019t have the power grid to support the additional homes nor do we have the water to supply the ever growing population demand. The local lake levels are the lowest I\u2019ve ever seen in my 26yrs of living in this great state. Water is going to be more expensive than gas in the future if we don\u2019t stop building so many new subdivisions.Planters will always be a great product and my favorite brand of nuts because of the variety they offer and the quality of their products that is the best in my opinion. They still provide a great product and a five star rating for their line of products.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "James", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Addictive and delicious", "content": "These roasted pecans are really tasty. reviews: {"author": "Rachel C.", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Satisfy Your Cravings Healthily", "content": "As a health-conscious individual always on the lookout for convenient and nutritious options, I was excited to try these bars, and they did not disappoint. Pure Protein has truly nailed it with the flavor of these bars. The lemon cake flavor is refreshingly tangy and perfectly balanced, with just the right amount of sweetness to satisfy your cravings without feeling heavy or overly indulgent. It\u2019s like enjoying a slice of lemon cake without the guilt.But what really sets these bars apart is their nutritional profile. Each bar is packed with 20 grams of protein, making it an excellent choice for fueling your body and keeping you feeling satisfied throughout the day. Protein is essential for muscle repair and growth, making these bars ideal for post-workout recovery or simply as a mid-day pick-me-up.What\u2019s more, Pure Protein Lemon Cake Bars are low in sugar and carbs, making them a smart choice for anyone watching their intake of these nutrients. With only a fraction of the sugar found in traditional snack bars, you can enjoy these guilt-free knowing you\u2019re making a healthy choice for your body.I also appreciate the convenience factor of these bars. Whether you\u2019re rushing between meetings, hitting the gym, or simply need a quick snack on the go, Pure Protein Lemon Cake Bars are the perfect solution. They\u2019re individually wrapped, making them easy to toss in your bag or desk drawer for whenever hunger strikes.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 25, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "chris pecile", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Good taste,good value", "content": "Along the lines of protein bars, these are very good. Granted, compared to a candy bar, maybe not, but these are protein bars. The ingredients are very good, high protein, low sugar. They are probably the cheapest yet highest quality protein bars on the market. Like I said, they are very good too, just don't expect a candy bar. Will continue to buy.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 20, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Moises", "rating": "4.0 ", "title": "Slightly better than average", "content": "This is a typical protein bar. 200 calories with the standard dense and chewy protein with a gritty texture on your teeth and a slightly bitter aftertaste. That type of protein bar has been pretty much boilerplate for years now. The only difference is the combination of nuts or gross chocolate it is covered in.While the protein component of this bar is old hat, the fact it is covered in cake frosting flavored coating makes it taste better than most. So I do prefer this over most bars that try rather unconvincingly to be like a candy bar. I think the addition of a sparse splatter of sprinkles is pointless though. I guess they want to really sell the birthday cake angle, but there are not enough sprinkles to matter and sprinkles are made with dyes that are extremely questionable healthwise so it would be better without them. But aside from flavor, the other selling point is it has a very reasonable fat to protein ratio. This fits my nutritional needs better than most. Seems like all protein products these days try to hide the fat content of their products. Since fat is not an issue or even preferred for keto, I find that most protein bars lately have been jacking up the fat content to improve flavor and texture then just slapping a keto-friendly stamp on the packaging and then only advertise the high grams of protein and low grams of sugar and then avoid mentioning fat anywhere on the box except the nutritional facts chart. Most products advertised as keto-friendly have way more fat than my diet can handle. The fat to protein ratio in this product is 5/20 which is pretty good in comparison to similar products available.I  also ordered the chocolate mint cookie and lemon cake flavors as a subscription which is have not tried yet but expect to be good based on the way the birthday cake tasted. I would have preferred to subscribe to the birthday cake flavor but some flavors were not available for subscription and save, birthday cake being one of them. Another bummer is there is a big price difference depending on flavor. Birthday cake and some of the chocolate flavors were $4 more than the average price and the cookies and cream were $27 per box so nearly double the cost, and also not available by subscription.  I guess it is all coming from different suppliers or whatever so it is what it is. If it were to become available for subscription I'd likely get it. They aren't revolutionary but they are certainly more pleasant to eat than the average. But protein bars have been around for a while and they pretty much have hit a plateau on flavor and texture, so that in mind, these are the best I've had in a while.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on August 9, 2023", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "paul v.", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "High protein", "content": "I feel that all these protein bars are a little overpriced and are taking advantage of people who love these things, but I was surprised by the amount of protein in these at 20g and the lower price than other bars of similar comparison. But the flavor and consistency and ingredients were good and make this well worth the money. I eat a bar before I workout and they seem to help me get through even the toughest days. Will definitely be buying more when I run out.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Amazon Customer", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Best value and taste bar", "content": "These are a daily for me. 200 Cals and 20g protein for $1.50 is hard to beat. They work well as an alternative to only having protein shakes. The flavor and texture is as good as most other options. Too 3 choice - lemon, cookies & cream, birthday cake", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 10, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Donna M", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Taste great", "content": "Love the pure protein brand and have been drinking the shakes in the morning which keep me satisfied.  These protein bars are also an easy grab if you are running errands on in need of a pick me up.  They taste like a brownie and keep me full for hours.  I will continue to purchase these on Amazon as they are impossible to find elsewhere.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 25, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "RC360 on YT", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Great grab and go snack to satisfy the cravings", "content": "I have a major sugar addiction, so trying to lose weight has been a lifetime of yo-yoing.Now when I feel that sugar craving I found that these protein bars (especially the birthday cake flavor) will help with that.They have enough protein and calories to be a meal replacement in a pinch but are best, for me, as a in between meal or on the run snack.Only 3 grams of sugar, 5 grams of fat and 20 grams of protein, great for after the gym as well.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 22, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Rachael Lanier", "rating": "4.0 ", "title": "Very good", "content": "I love how this has a very chocolately taste! title: Glico Pocky Chocolate Sticks, 1.41 Oz
description: About this item    Chocolate Cream Covered Biscuit Sticks    Great for snacks, lunch boxes, quick energy pick me ups and treats!
ingredients: 'WHEAT FLOUR, SUGAR, CHOCOLATE LIQUOR, BLEND OF VEGETABLE OIL, , WHOLE MILK POWDER, PALM OIL SHORTENING, CONTAINS 1 PERCENT OR LESS OF: COCOA BUTTER, SALT, ARTIFICIAL FLAVORS, YEAST, LECITHIN, POLYGLYCEROL, POLYRICINOLEATE, LEAVENING , MONOGLYCERIDE, SODIUM HYDROXIDE, PAPAIN.'
reviews: {"author": "Donuts", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Great tasting snack...if you get the Japanese Pocky", "content": "I bought these back in January and never got around to reviewing them. I had heard many people rave about a Japanese snack called Pocky so I figured I would try it out. Just like the description states, its a biscuit stick covered in chocolate. I wouldn't say the taste is mind boggling but its very easy to eat and virtually no mess, well, as long as the chocolate doesn't melt. Anyways, in case anyone is wondering, I ordered from a seller named Very asia (amazon.com/gp/help/seller/at-a-glance.html?ie=UTF8&isAmazonFulfilled=0&orderID=103-7071944-5595443&marketplaceSeller=1&seller=A3JW437I54SEI1). I believe it took around a 3 weeks to actually get to me (maybe it had to be imported) but when it did, it came well packed and not damaged whatsoever. I'm definitely considering re-stocking on this in the future if I can't find a local storeEDIT: Oct 11, 2012*****Inquire the type of pocky from seller before finalizing purchase*****So I decided to restock after I couldn't fight the craving anymore. Unfortunately the batch this time was not so good (ordered from different seller because it was cheaper and through Amazon Prime). What I received was not the picture shown on the front page (2 per pack japanese pocky), it was a 1 per pack pocky~ish thing from Thailand. In my opinion, the 1 giant pack compared to 2 smaller packs is definitely a step back. Packaging was fine and I ordered in October when the weather was a bit cooler aka no melted chocolate arriving at the front door. The sticks were coated in some type of thick chocolate that was a bit bitter to the taste, more similar to dark chocolate than milk chocolate. The original Japanese pocky melted almost immediately in your mouth, this one melts slowly as it sits in your mouth.Personally I like the taste of dark chocolate but not when used here as a pocky flavor. I also have terrible self control so I buy things that come in small portions in order to a) not eat everything at once and b) avoid making the fridge a mess by cluttering it with tons of opened items. I can honestly say that I won't be overeating when it comes to this batch of pocky because I and my stomach dislike it so much. I won't change my original rating because that still holds true for the Japanese pocky but if I were to rate only the Thailand pocky it would be a 3. The taste isn't \"terrible\" but its definitely not to my liking. If possible I will be uploading some pictures of what I received.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on June 23, 2011", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Aunt B", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Tasty Snack, Suggest not ordering in Summer Time", "content": "Tasty crunchy biscuit stick.  Not bitter, not too sweet.  Really like this single serving of Pocky.  The package says \"Chocolate Cream\" but it tastes more like dark chocolate to me (yum!)I see that others are disappointed with the portion of the product.  Please look at the images and Product Description before ordering to ensure you are getting what you want. I can only find these single serving boxes at one place that is about 40 miles away from my home.  It is convenient and awesome that I can shop at Amazon.com and find this treat at about the same price as at that store of mine (at time of writing this is $1.02 here at Amazon).The packaging at the time of this writing is a single serving which is 24 sticks. The box has a scored top so you can pull the cardboard back and have a container to hold the sticks in (see photo).  Tear the top of the sealed mylar  bag and the biscuit part is presented with the chocolate side down so you only need to touch the biscuit. [I added pictures in the Customer Images of the product]If you never had Pocky before, give them a try!!!  However, I warn you to consider the outside temperatures before ordering any chocolate products online.  I did not consider it as I ordered a couple boxes for myself (in Texas) and sent a few to a friend of mine in Idaho in the month of July.  I just did not think about it.  It was discouraging to learn my friend, who never tried Pocky, was met with a package of biscuit sticks that were melted together and has to eat them in broken pieces as they bust when she tries to pull them apart (the chocolate firmed up on her).  She still said she likes them, said the taste is great.At my house, my packages are also melted together; however, the chocolate is still soft as well... my house is about 80 degrees at the moment.  I can pull mine apart with a bit of a mess as the chocolate does as chocolate will do.  I don't mind too much as I get to lick my fingers off and feel like a little kid once more (awesome right?!?!).  But it isn't any sort of treat to give to a guest as the presentation is well... messy.  Unless that is cool with your guests then Go For It!!!!!That being said, I think this product is great if you like a bit of dark chocolate with a light, crispy biscuit.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2014", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "M. Thompson", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "I love this snack!", "content": "I'm not sure how you review something that's as subjective as taste, but suffice to say that if you like chocolate and graham cracker, you'll like this (it doesn't taste exactly like either of those, but that's the closest analogy for me).  The sticks themselves are a cracker of some kind, dipped in chocolate, with one end left just normal cracker to you don't get your fingers covered in chocolate while eating.Here's some of the nitty gritty details - each of the boxes contain two individually sealed packets, that contain probably 20 or so of the sticks.  The packets themselves are really cleverly designed, with a little slit cut in the folded part, you just grab both sides and pull, and it opens up the package without any hassle - gotta love Japanese product design!  :)  Another nice design touch is that when you open it properly the grabbing-side of the stick is right at the top.Each of the packets has 210 calories (90 from fat), and about 80mg of sodium - so in terms of snacks this is a pretty good option.  It does contain milk, wheat, soybeans and sheanut - so if any of these are an issue for you, then you'll want to pass.  It also says on the packaging that the facility they're manufactured in also processes eggs and peanuts - the product doesn't use either of them, but the disclosure is nice if you're particularly sensitive to either.Overall a great snack at a great price - the 10 pack really is 20 of the packets, so that's quite a few snacks.  One note, if you live in a hot climate, don't order them in the summer because they will melt together (in shipping)!  Duh!  :)", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2010", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "lyn hoult", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": null, "content": "daughter loves them and good value of price", "date": "Reviewed in the United Kingdom on February 28, 2017", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "carole", "rating": "2.0 ", "title": null, "content": "I bought a box of the Pocky and realised it said chocolate flavour, so it's not chocolate so I ordered a different box saying chocolate cream covered.  same Pocky came again chocolate flavour I agree with the others these were stuck together.  Not the usual Pocky we have bought from shops or comic conventions.", "date": "Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 26, 2021", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Ariel", "rating": "3.0 ", "title": null, "content": "Product doesn't look the same as the picture. It's from Thailand not Japan. either.", "date": "Reviewed in the United Kingdom on November 18, 2019", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "a j horton", "rating": "2.0 ", "title": null, "content": "Unfortunately they arrived all melted into each other. A disappointing Christmas present.", "date": "Reviewed in the United Kingdom on July 2, 2021", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "disco", "rating": "3.0 ", "title": null, "content": "Chocolate is slightly different and not as good as it tasted when we had it in Japan.", "date": "Reviewed in the United Kingdom on February 13, 2018", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}

reviews: {"author": "Precise Disarray", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "protein bars that are actually good. Love them as a \"sweet\" snack", "content": "I've been eating Power Crunch bars on and off for many years. I rely on them when I am cutting back on sugar. These make for an excellent treat if you happen to like the wafer style cookies (or even kitkats). You know.. that style that normally come in vanilla, strawberry, or chocolate. Except these are coated.  I would buy a pack, and gobble them all up. Loads of sugar and calories later with no other nutrient value, I would feel a little gross in my belly.  So Power Crunch really saves the day. I can use them as a treat, or as a means for boosting protein. I truly enjoy these, and dont just look at them as a consolation prize. I love vanilla, so this flavor is my favorite. I haven't met a variety I haven't liked, but the vanilla is my jam.Not too sweet, not too \"protein powder\" tasting (that can otherwise ruin a good looking healthy snack bar), and I can stop at one. Which is good because they are 220 calories a piece, not that far off from a regular candy bar. BUT, it isnt loaded with sugar (just 5 added sugars, same as a gummy vitamin), and it is a good size. I feel satisfied with one.The sweetness level is low on these. If you are used to eating lots of sweet things, then this may taste more bland. I find that true of most things when I switch from sugar laden diet to a sugar restricted diet. Takes awhile for taste buds to adjust. So keep that in mind if you are just starting off and are looking for treat alternatives.  If you have been cutting sugar, then this is a perfect level of sweet. Just enough to be tasty, yet not enough to be cloying. LOVE IT SO MUCH I would love to see the bar made into two sticks, or two squares.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2021", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Daniel Sanchez", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Satisfied hunger", "content": "Love this waffles, had to subscribe to the every 2 weeks. It\u2019s a great deal and very healthy. Very tasty", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 21, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Ana Paula", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "The Best protein snack!", "content": "I'm obsessed!!! The flavor reminds me of the sweet wafers I ate as a kid, but knowing that it's high in protein and not so high in sugars, make it the perfect choice for my sweet treats!!! I love them!!!!!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Liz", "rating": "4.0 ", "title": "Desert/in between meals", "content": "I have this delicious bar with my coffee and it fills me up until lunch.So tasty n filling yummy", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "j p", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Various flavors", "content": "My opinion only: I have tried all currently available flavors except cinnamon, chocolate chip cheesecake and coconut. Vanilla seems to be the best and it comes with 14g protein where all other flavors have 13g. I would not recommend any of the chocolate flavors especially the choc mint, unless you want to feel like someone poured battery acid in your stomach. Chocolate peanutbutter seems to be the easiest to tolerate if you have to go with a chocolate flavor and Red Devil's cake is pretty mild. The absolute worst flavors for me have been the strawberry: it has a very weird alcohol like smell to it, and salted caramel: this flavor has an identical odor to a Roach Motel. After Vanilla, I found I can tolerate the Peanutbutter flavor and find the Lemon Meringue to be oddly appealing although the coating on those are reminiscent of inadvertently getting sprayed in the face with Pledge. I heard there were limited releases of Orange and Key Lime, but never got to try those either. The fruit flavored ones seem to be a lot more crumbly than others; they do not hold together as well as Choc, Van and P'nut butter flavored ones. Do yourself a favor, put the entire box in the fridge. When it's time to have one, take it out of the fridge, remove the entire wrapper and break the entire bar into bite sized pieces before it warms up to room temp. Otherwise, you'll have melted whey everywhere and lose some of the protein you just paid for. Don't store them in your gym or handbag and don't plan to keep one in the car unless you live in a place with snowy winters. To try new flavors, go to Walmart and by the 5 bar box, then if you like that flavor, come back to Amazon and get the 12 bar box for the best price. I nearly bought the 12 bar Strawberry from Amazon but opted for the smaller 5 bar box at Wally's and I am so very glad I did because I don't think I could have choked 11 more Strawberry ones down after the first one. On to cheesecake, cinnamon and coconut!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 10, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Annette", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Tasty and guilt free dessert", "content": "Light and crispy, with a sweet vanilla taste.  I was pleasantly surprised at how good they are.  I am trying to increase my protein intake, and as a vegetarian this is not an easy task.  And I get to enjoy dessert without all the carbs and  a considerable amount of protein.Update:  These are still good, but do have a bit of a chalkiness texture to them, and they are VERY sweet.  I can only eat half a bar at a time.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 21, 2023", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "ErichWilliamBerger", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Best Tasting Protein Bar - Ever", "content": "I first encountered these in my local grocery store. Best taste overall in Vanilla, Dark Chocolate, Peanut Butter Creme, Chocolate Mint. I now buy these by the case on Amazon. One of these replaces at least one meal for me per day. Love 'em!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "CLWS", "rating": "3.0 ", "title": "Very crumbly and easily crushed", "content": "I had hoped these would taste better than they do based on recommendations. I quickly learned that these bars are very messy to eat. description: About this item    Strawberry flavor    Hi-Chew Strawberry sticks make a perfect "pick-me-up" Snack for on the go or at home    Hi-Chew is an explosion of real, fruity flavors with a long lasting chewy texture    Contains real fruit juices and purees, no artificial colors, gluten free, cholesterol-free, and 0g Trans fat    Hi-Chew has long been the #1 soft candy in Japan, and in recent years, has become a hit in the rest of Asia and America
ingredients: Glucose Syrup, Sugar, Vegetable Oil , Less than 2% of Gelatin, Natural and Artificial Flavors, Malic Acid, Citric Acid, Strawberry Juice Concentrate, Sucrose Fatty Acid Esters, Sorbitan Monostearate, Purple Carrot Juice , Soy Lecithin.
reviews: {"author": "John", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Hi-Chew Candy Sticks: Spooky Fun for Your Taste Buds!", "content": "Let me start by saying that I bought this Hi-Chew Candy Sticks Variety Pack for Halloween, and it turned out to be one heck of a flavorful haunted house for my taste buds. This assortment is like a candy cornucopia with a twist, and I'm here to break it down for you.First of all, the packaging gets extra points for its Halloween vibes. The box looks like it could have come straight from a witch's candy stash - vibrant colors and eerie illustrations that scream, \"Boo! I'm delicious!\" It's so tempting that it's almost scary.Now, on to the candy sticks themselves. The variety in this pack is amazing. There are eight different flavors, and it's like a spooky roulette every time you reach for one. I mean, who wouldn't be intrigued by the idea of mystery-flavored taffy? It's like playing Russian Roulette, but with much tastier consequences.The texture of these Hi-Chew sticks is where the magic happens. They're soft and chewy, with a satisfying taffy-like consistency that leaves you pulling stretchy candy ghosts from your mouth. It's like a workout for your jaw, but the payoff is sweet (literally).The flavors are truly a mixed bag of Halloween tricks and treats. You've got classics like strawberry and green apple, which are like the familiar faces at a costume party. Then there are surprises like lychee and mango, which are like the guests who show up wearing the most unexpected costumes \u2013 exotic and exciting.The taste is where the real fun begins. Some flavors are so spot-on that you'd think Hi-Chew had a witch's brew in their candy-making laboratory. Others might be a bit more acquired, but hey, that's what Halloween is all about - trying new things and getting a little spooked in the process.As for the sweetness, it's just right. Not too overpowering, so you can indulge without feeling like you're in a candy coma. You can snack on these bad boys while watching your favorite horror movies, and they'll never steal the show. They're the perfect co-stars.Now, some may say that Hi-Chew Candy Sticks are a bit pricey for Halloween candy, but remember, you're not just buying candy \u2013 you're investing in a spooktacular experience that's sure to thrill both your taste buds and your party guests.In conclusion, the Hi-Chew Candy Sticks Variety Pack is the ultimate Halloween candy for those who like a little adventure with their sweet treats. It's the trick-or-treating experience you've been missing in your life. Whether you're handing them out to trick-or-treaters or enjoying them all by yourself, these Hi-Chew sticks are a winner. Just be prepared for some ghoulishly good times and maybe even a few taste bud scares along the way!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on October 24, 2023", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "R. Geist", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "I live in the US and I am not normally a candy guy -- that said -  this Japanese candy is awesome description below", "content": "So,  I live in the US and  this candy is fairly hard to find here unless you know about it or encounter it in the candy section of your world market.But I happened on it at a family run homestyle Japanese restaurant and it is really unusual but amazingly yummy.  AND USEFUL for someone looking for a fun way to produce natural saliva from a good but tangy flavor.First know,  I am not normally a candy guy, but I found the taste and texture of this so unusual and yummy I wanted others outside of Japan or other countries where it is widely sold and marketed to know about it.  It comes packaged like a pack of chewing gum in blocks.  But it is not gum.  though its texture is like that of gum initially,  really flavorful classic Grape Kool aid flavor gum.  It is also chewey like gum though it does over time get softer and softer and it is meant to be swallowed.  But what really makes its so neat is that one the flavor is reminiscent of that childhood perfect candy grape flavor and where it is sweet and tangy and makes your mouth water.  Also it chews just like gum except the flavor does not get less and less like gum.  it stays pungent with a nice mix of sweet and tangy Grape flavor until it gets so soft you just swallow it or you can let it slowly dissolve in your mouth.  I have had to be on some medications that can cause my mouth to get really dry and very few things can move my latent salivary glands to produce more saliva.  And while this product does have sugar in it.  it is still the best way I have found to produce my own moisture.  Also one or two pieces can really be satisfying and you have a nice flavor in your mouth and you do not need to keep eating the candy.  I have never seen another item like this where the texture starts out like a bubble gum block and then you chew on it to get this explosion of Grape Kool aide flavor that never lessens until you swallow it.  its like the gum you always wanted but never got in that the flavor stays and you can swallow it when you are done chewing.  Grape is by far and away my favorite flavor though I have tried strawberry and Pear  with friends and  some like the strawberry better.  None of the flavors taste bad.  in fact that is the other cool thing is that the whole theme of their flavor variety is a sweet and tangy take on natural fruit flavors.  I have given a piece to many unsuspecting people at this point and almost every time,  they either immediately say \"WOW! what is this stuff?\"  or they come back and make a point to ask me about it later. I even gave it to a guy in my neighborhood grocery store and he ran up to me the next time I came in the store and took down all the information on what the candy was and how and where he can get it.  Other than Amazon where they charge a fair price for a full case of the stuff -- usually around 11 dollars.  You might find the candy in single form for about a dollar and some change a package -- the case comes with ten packs and I cannot stress how fun and good this is.  If anyone who is reading this is looking for a great way to occasionally pop a treat in their mouth that will produce a ton of their own moisture, its great for that too,  You just chew it a bit then let it sort of sit there like candy gum and it will just gush out its flavor. If I had to bet which would be the most popular flavor I would say it would be grape.  But then I always had a weakness for certain childhood flavors of good kool-aid.  if you wanted to put a sweet tangy grape taste in your mouth that you could chew on like gum for a while and then either just suck on it and let it shed its flavor just like it was new or to chew it till it was so hot, chewed and soft that you could swallow it.  This is your candy.  I could have used  the taffy texture for this but it really is not sticky until the very end when one might be prone to swallow it.  -- of course coming through Amazon,  it came quickly well packaged and ready to go. totally fun thing to have around the house to put in a travel bag for something sweet to have as a change from sugar free gum which i also carry.  and a fun treat that will totally mesmerize western kids of all ages.  if you look at the individual piece it even has neat detailing as the outside is a milky white but in the center there is purple center for grape, red for strawberry and so forth.  Very reminiscent of Jelly Bellies.  if someone eats healthy most of the time but are looking for fun treats that can satisfy for a while with just a piece or two and are unique -- I would definitely try this candy out.  It is very Japanese with its focus on details. and that the texture of the candy is as cool as the taste.  and the grape taste is clean is that makes any sense.  no super gross chemical aftertaste.  If you know your taste is different then perhaps you can try something other than Grape but for me Grape is the best and it seems to have the most universal appeal. I wanted to check out and see if they had a mango or orange flavor too.  I would love to give these out on halloween if they had a smaller pack to give out.  In my opinion its a cannot miss.  maybe you will love it maybe you will just like it,  but I would be shocked if you did not at least really like it.  And all this from a guy who is not into candy and usually only has sugar free spearmint gum.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2013", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "SIR R D M", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Best Bananna Chewy Around!", "content": "Great flavor & texture!!!!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 7, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Amazon Customer", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "I love these", "content": "I love these and we can't get them at stores where I live. reviews: {"author": "Chris Mendes", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Classic Favorite", "content": "Cheddar Goldfish Crackers have been a staple in our household for as long as I can remember. They have become his go-to snack, and for good reason!First and foremost, the cheddar flavor is absolutely delicious. It has just the right amount cheesy goodness that keeps you coming back more. The crackers have a satisfying crunch that adds an extra level of enjoyment to every bite. Whether it's a quick snack on the go or a part of lunchtime, these crackers always hit the spot.Not only are Cheddar Goldfish Crackers tasty, but they are also made with high-quality ingredients. As a parent, it gives me peace of mind knowing that my son is snacking on a product that is free from artificial preservatives and flavors. It's comforting to see him enjoy a snack that I can feel good about.The portability of these crackers is also worth mentioning. They come in convenient resealable bags, making it easy to take them on road trips, picnics, or simply pack them for school lunches. The individual fish shapes are fun and make snack time even more enjoyable for kids and adults alike.Furthermore, Cheddar Goldfish Crackers are not only a hit with my son but with the whole family. It's a snack that brings everyone together, whether it's sharing a handful during movie nights or munching on them during playdates. They have a universal appeal that makes them a crowd-pleaser for all ages.In conclusion, Cheddar Goldfish Crackers are a classic favorite in our household. With their delicious cheddar flavor, quality ingredients, and convenient packaging, they continue to be a snack that my son loves and we can all enjoy. If you haven't tried them yet, I highly recommend giving them a go - they are sure to become a staple in your pantry too!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Shanique", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Great value", "content": "Love these, great value. She indulges in this activity during the autumn months, coinciding with the heightened seal activity in the northeastern region where she resides. title: POPCORNERS Sea Salt Popped Corn Snacks, Gluten Free, Non-GMO, Single-Serve 1oz bags (Pack of 40)
description: About this item    CONTAINS: 40 - 1 oz snack packs of crunchy and wholesome popped-corn chip snacks: Sea Salt    WHOLESOME SNACKS: PopCorner's delicious popped corn snacks are drizzled in sunflower oil with a pinch of sea salt, our chips are made with non-GMO corn and never fried, are gluten-free, and nut-free. Just simple ingredients for better flavor!    SIMPLE INGREDIENTS: Made with only three ingredients, and no artificial flavors, colors, or preservatives- PopCorner's Sea Salt Contains just 3 ingredients: Yellow Corn, sunflower oil & sea salt    TESTED AND TRUE: Non GMO Project Verified, Gluten Free, Kosher, Nut Free & Vegan - a good alternative to fruit snacks    Convenient on-the-go snacks great for a busy lifestyle, at work, kids' lunch snacks and much more
ingredients: Yellow Corn ,Sunflower Oil, Sea Salt.
reviews: {"author": "Libby", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Tasty....and only three ingredients: corn, oil and salt!", "content": "In the convenience food category, these are the best combination of healthy snack and tasty snack that I've found.  They have just 3 ingredients: yellow corn, sunflower oil and sea salt.  In one bag (one portion per 1.1 oz bag, which is more than you'd think) there is only 6 grams of fat and 135 mg of sodium.  If you've been looking at nutrition labels you'll know this is great.  And very importantly, they're delicious.  They taste very much like popcorn made into a chip.  The sea salt is my favorite because it has the fewest ingredients (healthiest)and has that pure popcorn taste without the addition of artificial flavors.  The box of 40 sells for 17.14 (you can't beat Amazon!)which comes to about 43 cents per bag. I first discovered these at Costco and bought a big box of the individual bags without knowing what I was getting.....hoping to discover a tasty healthier snack.  Since discovering them I haven't seen them available anywhere else except through Amazon.  Thanks Amazon for giving us a great product at a great price!!!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on April 23, 2013", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Ken M", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Excellent snack at a good price.", "content": "This review is on the 'Sea Salt' flavor. For a serving size of a 1.1 ounce bag, the facts are: 3.5g fat, 0g trans fat, 0g saturated fat, 190mg sodium, 24g carbohydrate, 6% DV of iron. The ingredients: Yellow Corn, Sunflower Oil, Sea Salt.The date code on the bags I received was for 10 months onto the future, I have no worry about being able to finish them by that time.They are popped corn that has somehow been pressed into the shape of a fried corn chip. They are a little crisp mixed with the texture of popped corn, meaning they are not dry and as brittle as a corn chip. Medora did some kind of magic on the pressed chips to make them taste a bit like real corn chips. All in all, I was pleasantly surprised with the snack-ability, good job with that.I ate two bags of these and then placed an order for another 40 pack, of a different flavor. That is my endorsement.Enjoy.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on June 28, 2013", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "M.NPR", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "PopCorners are poppin' with flavor", "content": "I saw these chips and had to buy them since I purchase Popchips by the case on a regular basis. I assumed these were the same except made with corn. I was right. They are delicious! I enjoy plain corn chips or plain multigrain chips and these too are plain and simple with lots of flavor. I don't think these need all the elaborate flavoring (i.e. Nacho cheese, spicy salsa, triple cheese, etc.). They are great for my kids lunch and a nice indulgence for me if I eat a sandwich for lunch. I highly recommend these.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2010", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Joan M Searcy", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "YUM!", "content": "If you like popcorn and need to limit how many bowlfuls you devour at one sitting, this is a great product for you! These little bags have just the right amount of salty, crunchy popcorniliciousness and by getting an entire case, you have lots to enjoy, some to share, and plenty to take with you wherever you go. Best snack out there -- only 140 low-fat calories per bag, in 5 flavors.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2014", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Willa", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Housewife", "content": "Our family loves this product, and my daughter likes it especially because she must eat gluten free foods, and this is good for her.  We have only been able to get this product at a rest stop on the turnpike, and was so glad to find it on the internet.I came back from vacation, and wanted to make another order, and I discovered that the price had doubled.  I was very disappointed  and if that is the case, I will not be ordering it again.We do love the popcorn taste and the seasalt makes it taste so good.  I would like to write to the company and see how to find out about the price of the 40 bags.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on June 19, 2012", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Christie", "rating": "4.0 ", "title": "Natural, Healthy, tasty snack.", "content": "These were surprisingly good. I've tried the ever famous \"popchips\" which, although they were good, didn't seem as healthy as these.These have a few ingredients including corn, sunflower oil and sea salt. They are soft like popcorn all around. They still have a slight crunch like a tortilla chip, but after the initial crunch, it's like a piece of popcorn. The taste is authentic and very good! Just enough salt for the sea salt flavor.Highly recommend to anyone looking for a good snack to fill up time. 140 Calories in a bag, and not much else.Ordering the jalapeno to try, too.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on May 25, 2014", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "NF1031", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Hooray a popcorn alternative for someone with digestive issues!", "content": "I had my large intestine removed and to avoid blockages I stay away from hard to digest foods and things with seeds including popcorn. I miss popcorn the most out of all the things I can't have. I also watch my gluten intake as it slows down digestion. I came across these chips and feel like I found my happy medium! These are light, easy to chew, have no seeds and taste alot like the flavor I am missing from my popcorn snacking! The subscribe and save is a great deal. I got a box full of these chips that will last me until my next delivery! Love these!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2014", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "TY", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "The best salty snacks", "content": "These are my favorite salty snacks! I first encountered them on a JetBlue flight and immediately went searching for them. They have a delightful crunchy texture with the taste of popcorn. I've also tried the kettle corn flavor, which is okay, but the caramel was kind of weird and not for me.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2013", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}

Certainly there are better donuts to be had.  Maybe it's nostalgia; my father would sometimes wake up early on a Saturday morning and take a walk up to the grocery store to buy a morning newspaper, cigarettes and a box of donuts for us kids to enjoy when we woke up.  Not these particular donuts, however.  These weren't carried by the grocery store, they featured Hostess and Dolly Madison back then.When my son was young he latched onto a box of these while my wife and I were shopping.  I couldn't say NO to him, they were on a table at the back corner of the store and priced at $1.  It would be my first experience with \"The Chocolate Wax Donut\".  And though I don't often eat these anymore my son sure loves them.So what's so good about them?  Well, in my book it's pretty simple.  First off you have to put them in the refrigerator so that they don't melt because then they are slimy.  Keep them good and waxy!  Next, pour yourself a tall glass of milk.  But leave some room in the glass.  Break the donut in half and dip it into the milk.  Hold it there for 2-3 seconds to get it good and saturated, then remove from the glass and hold it with the soaked end facing up so that the milk continues to filter into the cake inside.  Now enjoy!  It just tastes so good.  Enjoy!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2021", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Robert Goldman", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "The diet killer. reviews: {"author": "Quarter4Scale", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Tasty very tasty exactly 62g per bar", "content": "Writing this review as soon as I received my bars and took a bite. To me, they are very very tasty. Granted I haven't had a regular candy bar in years so I don't know what a regular bar really tastes like these days. And frankly, I won't enjoy a regular candy bar knowing I'll be eating junk and sugar that's bad for my health.  As far as protein bars go, I don't detect any aftertaste or anything weird whatsoever. They taste entirely normal to me and offer a perfect mix of saltiness and sweetness with that unique and unmistakable taste of peanuts. At one point, I really enjoyed Power Crunch peanut butter creme protein wafer bars but even those had an unmistakable artificial sweetener taste to them. These don't taste artificial at all so I do believe their claim that these don't contain any artificial sweeteners. I love love love these. Bye bye power Crunch. In fact, these are dangers to have around cuz I might eat too many at a time. They will be perfect for my international flight coming up. I suspect I won't be meeting my daily protein goals by just eating the meals provided by the airline.The only thing is , I'm pretty sure the peanut butter coating will melt if these bars are kept in a backpack/ container/ glove compartment in hot weather. Yummy!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 12, 2024", "verified": "( "}; {"author": "bae", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Bit pricey but good, low sugar protein bar", "content": "These bars are a bit pricey for a box of 12, but they actually taste decent, and it's a pretty good low-sugar option.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 24, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "SQUiD808", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Tasty", "content": "Yo these are super good idk how they did it", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 25, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "jorban", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Indulgent Flavor, Wholesome Ingredients", "content": "If you're like me, always on the lookout for a tasty snack that doesn't compromise on nutrition, then look no further than the KIND Protein MAX Sweet & Salty Caramel Peanut Crisp Snack Bars. These bars are a true joy, offering a delightful combination of flavor and wholesome ingredients that will satisfy your cravings without any guilt.First and foremost, let's talk about taste. These bars are an absolute treat for the taste buds, with a rich and indulgent flavor profile that makes them taste more like a decadent dessert than a protein-packed snack. The sweet and salty combination of caramel, sea salt, and peanuts is simply irresistible, offering a burst of deliciousness in every bite. It's hard to believe that something so delicious can also be so nutritious!What sets these bars apart is their thoughtful ingredient list. Peanuts take center stage as the #1 ingredient, providing a natural source of protein and a rich, nutty flavor that shines through with every bite. This focus on real, wholesome ingredients is truly refreshing, and it's evident from the first taste that these bars are made with care and attention to quality.In addition to being delicious, these bars are also nutritious. With 20g of protein per serving, they're the perfect snack for fueling up on the go or satisfying hunger between meals. Plus, they're keto-friendly, with low carbs and low sugar, making them an excellent option for those following a low-carb lifestyle. And with 0g of added sugar and just 1g of total sugar, you can enjoy them guilt-free, knowing that you're making a smart choice for your health.But it's not just about what's in these bars \u2013 it's also about what's not. If it was not necessary, KIND did not include it. They're gluten-free, kosher,  contain no sugar alcohols or artificial sweeteners and no GMOs, if those sorts of things matter to you. This means you can feel good about enjoying them, knowing that you're nourishing your body with wholesome, clean ingredients.In terms of convenience, these bars are amazing. Whether you're grabbing a quick snack on the go or fueling up for a busy day, they're the perfect option for busy lifestyles. They're portable, easy to stash in your bag or desk drawer, and ready to enjoy whenever hunger strikes. Plus, with their satisfying texture and indulgent flavor, they'll keep you satisfied and energized throughout the day.Overall, I can't recommend the KIND Protein MAX Sweet & Salty Caramel Peanut Crisp Snack Bars highly enough. They're delicious, nutritious, and convenient \u2013 everything you could want in a snack. Whether you're looking for a post-workout pick-me-up or a tasty treat to enjoy on the go, these bars have you covered. Treat yourself to the goodness of real ingredients and indulgent flavor with KIND Protein MAX bars \u2013 you won't be disappointed!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024", "verified": "( "}; {"author": "KH99", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Excellent protein bars", "content": "I was surprised to find that, for a 12 pack box of bars, they're actually quite sizable. Each bar is, I would say, perhaps twice the size width-wise of an average granola bar and serves as a reasonably filling snack. In terms of flavor, KIND struck a good balance here. The peanuts and caramel are both definitely present, yet at a good balance so that neither of those flavors feels overpowering. The peanuts themselves also live up to the \"crisp,\" with each bite having an appreciable crunch to it.I'm also happy to say that, for protein bars that emphasize peanuts so much, I expected that they would be messier to eat, but the bars actually hold together very well even as you bite into them. As a side note, these are definitely fresh with a far off expiration date, so they'll keep in the cabinet for a good while. In my case, I ordered these in early February, and the listed expiration date is in December. I really hate protein powders. They just don't taste good with water, and I can't drink milk so it really limis my options to get the protein I need.Pure protein bars don't have the highest overall protein out of all the bars out there. If you really want the purest form of protein, eat egg whites or lean meat (Chicken/Turkey Breast, Beef, etc).Ok, that being said, you cannot carry eggs around, that's where this bar comes into picture. It has excellent amount of protein (20g) and low carbohydrate. It tastes absolutely delicious. I have always used (about 4-5 bars in a week) DeTour and Myoplex Protein bars. Detour has about 30g and Myoplex has about 25g of protein but their carb content is higher as well, and so is the calories. I am trying to lose weight, so I am watching both proteins and carbs, also doing cardio 5 times a week. I am not a nutritionist, but I am pretty sure the contents of these protein bars contain mono-saturated fats, which is not so good for our health. So, limit the use of these products as much as you can. Also, it has whey and sugar alcohols (sugar replacement), which can upset stomach for some people. I had that trouble with Detour but got used to it. The important thing is that you drink atleast 8 fl oz of water while taking this. Also, please limit your intake of these bars to 1 per day due to sugar alcohol presence.Recently, I have done a lot of research and it's best to eat whole grains and vegatables/lean meat to lose weight, instead of taking supplements. Good luck to you all, I think these 12 bars will last me atleast 3 weeks.I took one star off just because I do not want to encourage myself or anyone else to get addicted to these bars. Otherwise, it tastes just like a chocolate.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2010", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Sandra K. I've had to contact Amazon every month and they either give me a refund or ship another box. One time, they gave me a refund so I could reorder and the reorder was wrong too.  I only got one box.  If two boxes get delivered, it is a good value for something that tastes good and is enjoyed by my family. But the protein/calorie content is highest I have seen; they are fairly natural even if all protein bars are highly-processed food; the protein is a balanced mix of whey protein and a smaller amount of soy and other sources; they leave you satisfied (true meal replacement).The recipe has changed recently to being entirely naturally flavored. As of this writing, the graphics on the Amazon listing still show the \"naturally and artificially flavored\" label from the older packaging, but I received the new ones (naturally flavored). title: Quest Nutrition Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Protein Bars, High Protein, Low Carb, Gluten Free, Keto Friendly, 12 Count
description:
About this item    YOU DESERVE A SPECIAL TREAT: The Quest Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Protein Bar tastes like a scoop of cookie dough fresh from the bowl. Only our version is packed with chocolate flavored chips and has 21g protein 4g net carbs and 1g sugar    UNWRAP COMPLETE PROTEINS: Quest Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Protein Bars are made with complete, dairy-based proteins to provide your body with 9 essential amino acids.    FIBER IS YOUR FRIEND: Each Quest Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Protein Bar has 12g of fiber to provide your body with a more complete macro profile.    SWEET WITHOUT ADDED SUGAR: Enjoy the rewarding taste of Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough without worrying about added sugars. The Quest Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Protein Bar has no added sugars.    COMFORT FOODS FOR ANYTIME CRAVINGS: The Quest Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Protein bar is a sweet treat, without all the sugar, you can enjoy whenever you want to satisfy your sweet tooth.    Box contains 12 Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough flavored Quest Protein Bars    20 Gram of protein per bar    
   All natural and Gluten free Delicious and convenient Packed with fiber to make you feel full Helps with digestion and weight loss   Show more
reviews: {"author": "lV", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Protein, Fiber and Taste", "content": "The Quest Cookies and Cream protein bar is packed with 21g of protein, 13 g of fiber, only 1 g of sugar, 190 calories and a pleasant taste. The bar is a little harder than cookie dough but is still soft and chewy. It is not as sweet as cookie dough but still tastes somewhat sweet and more like a treat than a high protein, high fiber product.Quest accomplishes the good taste without all the sugar by using the sugar alcohol Erythritol.Erythritol has been shown to be safe as it is excreted from the body in an unchanged form and is less likely to upset the digestive tract as it goes through the bloodstream and is excreted in urine rather than being passed through the digestive tract where other sugar alcohols can be fermented, resulting in digestive issues. Additionally, Erythritol does not result in increases in blood sugar and insulin (important for diabetics or those trying to lose weight or with insulin resistance).The ingredients indicate that these bars contain almonds. I can't digest nuts or legumes, however I don't taste the nuts and have not had any issues with digesting these bars, which has made me happy, because almonds have a number of nutritional benefits, but I'm guessing the amount present is probably pretty small, although they rank relatively high on the ingredient list.In terms of the proteins and fiber, Quest uses a blend of milk protein isolate and whey protein isolate, which has been shown to have a good yield and blend of amino acids. The fiber is in the form of polydextrose, a common prebiotic fiber.Overall, Quest has found a formula to make a tasty nutrition bar that is both high in protein and high in fiber (a benefit that most protein bars don't include), while being very low in sugar. Nutritionally these bars seem to offer a lot of benefits as well as being a tasty treat.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Rene Grigorian", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Great snack! Love it", "content": "I have been eating Quest bars for a long time and these are my absolute favorite flavor. I love the taste of these and the fact that this keeps me full in between meals is a great plus. For someone who just started on his Keto journey, these have been a great snacking option when I eat my lunch and also after dinner before I fast from 7 pm - 12 pm the next day.Highly recommend these to anyone. Great product", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 8, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Sarah B.", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Favorite Protein Bars", "content": "Quest protein bars are by far the best. No chalky taste like other protein bars, low sugar to fit into any macro diet, and taste delicious! They're are so easy for on the go for breakfast or a post work out treat.This is a great alternative to satisfying hunger. Buying in bulk is much more reasonable vs.the price per bar you find in the local grocery stores.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 8, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Alana ", "rating": "4.0 ", "title": "Pretty decent", "content": "These have a pretty good amount of protein and fewer carbs than many other bars which I like. The cookie dough flavor is not horrible but certainly not my favorite i\u2019ve had. It\u2019s quite hard/chewy and has strong artificial sweetener taste. That being said, I will definitely finish the box but probably stick to the crispy Quest bars going forward!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 12, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Tom", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Like a healthy cookie", "content": "Quest Nutrition Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Protein Bars are a delicious and convenient snack option for anyone looking to fuel their active lifestyle. Packed with 21 grams of protein and only 1 gram of sugar, these bars provide a satisfying and guilt-free treat. These squares were less \"snap, crackle, pop\" and more like a casual stroll through a library \u2013 quiet, but not in a good way. I was expecting a snappy texture, but these squares were more chill than my grandma's Sunday afternoon crossword session.Now, let's chat about the flavor, or should I say the MIA flavor? Organic white cheddar sounds fancy, right? Well, these squares made me question my taste buds. I was looking for a cheese explosion, but it was more like a cheese murmur. I mean, come on, Annie! Where's the cheese party you promised?And can we talk about the uniformity? These squares are so perfectly shaped; I feel like I'm snacking on cheese-flavored graph paper. I miss the days when snack crackers had character, you know, like they'd been through a wild party in the snack factory.Look, Annie's, I love your commitment to being all organic and stuff, but let's not forget the snack part of the snack. Next time, maybe add a little more cheese and a sprinkle of snack rebellion. ETA: White Cheddar=awesome", "content": "I had never tried these before I bought them from Amazon.  -A bit risky, yes, I know.  But with the majority of reviews being GREAT, I figured why not? The texture is softer and crisp; not hard/gritty, like Pop Chips' Kettle version can be.  The kettle corn flavor is authentic, and isn't just a flavor coating...the entire chip is flavorful.  Although, I do think that they could cut back on the salt just a little.  There's a salty aftertaste that gets stronger as you eat more.  They're still delicious and I would definitely buy again, but it would be nice to not have as much of a salty aftertaste.Overall, if you're looking for a sweet yet salty low fat snack, give these a try!ETA: Amazon only allows one review, even though I've ordered the different flavors separately, so I'm adding in my opinion on the White Cheddar flavor:Ever tried Smartfood White Cheddar Popcorn? Be careful, you might just get addicted.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 24, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Julius A Heyne", "rating": "4.0 ", "title": "Nerds Gummy Clusters: A 4-Star Blast of Berry Crunch and Tang", "content": "Nerds Gummy Clusters, in their Very Berry flavor, are a fun and tasty twist on the classic candy. While they weren't quite a home run for me, they definitely offer a satisfying crunch-and-chew experience with a berrylicious punch. Here's my honest take, earning them a solid 4-star rating:Pros:Textural Delight: The combination of crunchy Nerds candy surrounding a soft, chewy gummy center is undeniably fun. Each bite delivers a satisfying contrast that keeps you coming back for more.Berrylicious Explosion: The Very Berry flavor mix is vibrant and refreshing. It's not overly sweet, with a nice balance of tartness and fruity sweetness that hits the spot for berry lovers.Resealable Convenience: The 8-ounce bag comes with a handy resealable closure, perfect for portion control or saving some for later. No more gummy fingers rummaging for the last bite!Fun for Kids and Adults: Nerds Gummy Clusters appeal to a wide range of ages. My inner child definitely enjoyed the playful combination of textures and flavors, while still holding some interest for my adult palate.Cons:Uneven Flavor Distribution: The Nerds candy on the outside tends to be more concentrated in some clusters than others. This can lead to occasional bites that are mostly gummy with no crunchy punch.Artificial Aftertaste: While the initial flavor is enjoyable, there's a lingering artificial aftertaste that can take away from the overall experience. It's not overpowering, but it's noticeable.Price Point: Compared to other gummy candies, Nerds Gummy Clusters seem a bit pricey for the quantity you get. This might make them more of an occasional treat than a regular snack.Overall:Nerds Gummy Clusters are a tasty and fun twist on the classic candy, offering a satisfying mix of textures and a vibrant berry flavor. However, some uneven flavor distribution and an artificial aftertaste hold them back from a perfect score. They're still a worthy treat for kids and adults alike, but you might want to grab them on sale or as a special indulgence.Rating: 4 out of 5 starsTip: If you find the artificial aftertaste off-putting, try pairing the gummies with a glass of water or unsweetened tea. It can help wash away the lingering sweetness.I hope this review gives you a good sense of what to expect from Nerds Gummy Clusters!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Pedro", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Very tasty!", "content": "It\u2019s chewy it\u2019s perfect and if you want a low price on candy here is the spot!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 29, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "P Wong", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "SOOO GOOD", "content": "I absolutely love the Nerds Gummy Clusters Candy.
