title: ROYCE' Nama Chocolate "Champagne Pierre Mignon"
description: About this item    MAKE EVERY MOMENT SPECIAL: Truffle chocolate is synonymous with luxury chocolate. ROYCE' Nama Chocolate is characterized by its soft and silky smooth texture. The fresh cream from Hokkaido, Japan is what makes this extraordinary! Celebrate special moments with chocolates that are sure to impress!    INCREDIBLY LUSCIOUS CHOCOLATE: ROYCE' Nama Chocolate "Champagne Pierre Mignon" is a confection made with milk chocolate and fresh cream, and lightly infused with champagne. Pierre Mignon is highly regarded for its high quality and delicate aroma which blends well with our milk chocolate. It is the perfect treat for celebrating with friends and family!    BLISSFUL TREAT FOR YOURSELF: Experience a treat for the senses with exceptionally rich, creamy, and flavorful chocolates. Elegant and fruity, ROYCE' Nama Chocolate "Champagne Pierre Mignon" is the ideal treat for those who like the finer things in life. Indulge yourself after a long day or surprise your friends with this delicious chocolate treat from ROYCE'.    PERFECT FOR SHARING: Each box contains 20 pieces of chocolate. There may be enough to share, but we wont blame you if theres nothing left before guests can even take a seat.This melt-in-you-mouth chocolate will satisfy the chocolate cravings of a wife, husband, girlfriend, boyfriend, grandparent, friend, or work colleague.    HOW JAPAN DOES CHOCOLATE: ROYCE' Chocolate takes immense pride in producing our confections in Hokkaido, an agricultural capital and gourmet hub in Japan. Our credo is to create top-notch chocolate selections in Hokkaido using only the finest ingredients sourced both locally in Japan and internationally from different countries. We want to entice everyone's palate through the Japanese principles of excellence and detail-oriented craftsmanship.

title: Original Crispy Seaweed Snacks by Nora | Low-Carb Asian Snack | Vegan, Gluten-Free, Non-GMO Verified | 6-Pack
description: About this item    SEAWEED SNACK Delicate but satisfying, Nora Crispy Seaweed will send your tongue spinning. Crispy and crunchy like a potato chip, yet low-carb and gluten-free, Original Crispy Seaweed is the ultimate guilt-free snack with just 3g carbs per serving! Pack of 6.    SUSHI ON-THE-GO Sushi, and other Asian cuisines, have long been foodie-favorites, and now you can grab our Nora Crispy Seaweed and enjoy that bold umami flavor on-the-go! Savor our light, crispy and flavorful vegan snack-youll keep coming back for more!    HEALTHY & SUSTAINABLE SNACK Did you know seaweed is one of the most nutrient dense vegetables on the planet, high in vitamins A, B6, and B12, as well as protein, iron, and fiber, and also one of the worlds most sustainable crops? Vegan snack is fully renewable - and delicious!    PREMIUM INGREDIENTS For thousands of years, Korean families have been harvesting seaweed, so we leave it to the experts! At Nora, we source our nori from farms in Korea, selecting only the finest, high-quality product available. Made with Rice Bran oil, a heart-healthy oil with 0g Trans-fat.    OUR STORY The simple truth is, we at Nora just love to eat seaweed snacks! So, we decided to share all this umami goodness with the worlds most discriminating and adventurous snackers - you! One taste and we think your taste buds will agree that Nora is like a trip through Asia, no passport required.

reviews: {"author": "Kevin L", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "These Sour Cream and Onion Pringles were fresh and a good deal for the money.", "content": "Sometimes it's hard to find good deals on chips these days unless you buy a large bulk. I don't like to buy too much at one time because the chips will often go stale before I eat them all. I also don't like the current pricing for most chips on Amazon and in the locals stores here in 2023. I found this 1 dozen pack of Pringles sour cream Grab and Go size stacks for a great price. They were well under $1 per can and that is about 1/3 of the price for them in the local stores. I just ate my first can of them. They were fresh with an expiration date late in 2024. There were a few broken chips in the bottom of the cans from shipping but only a few. You always have to worry about that with pringles because they are notorious for having broken chips. Nothing worse than a canister of Pringles dust! So far these look great. These shipped fast and showed up fresh and in great condition. As far as sour cream and onion chips go, Pringles are on the milder end of the flavor spectrum. They have a mild sour cream and onion taste and are pretty mellow. To me they have less flavor than Lay's, Ruffles, or Utz sour cream and onion chips. That is a good thing to some people because some other brands might have too much sour cream or onion. I like them all. To me these seem less salty than Lay's or Ruffles which is a good thing.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2023", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Jason G", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Excellent on the go snack", "content": "I enjoy having these for a quick snack on the go. Small but enough Pringles to fill up on. Easy to stack and store. Excellent flavor. They were very fresh too.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 20, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "John", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Snacking Bliss in a Variety Pack!", "content": "The Pringles Potato Crisps Variety Pack is an absolute snack-time delight! With 16 conveniently sized cans, it's perfect for lunch breaks, office munchies, and keeping the kids satisfied on the go.What sets Pringles apart is their iconic shape and satisfying crunch. Each crisp is consistently delicious, and this variety pack offers a medley of flavors to please everyone's palate.From classic Original to tantalizing Sour Cream & Onion, there's something for everyone in this pack. The variety ensures you'll never get bored, and it's great for sharing or mixing and matching your favorite flavors.The grab-and-go convenience is a game-changer. These stackable cans are easy to carry, and their resealable lids keep your chips fresh for later. No more worrying about crushed chips at the bottom of your bag!Whether you're a seasoned Pringles enthusiast or trying them for the first time, this variety pack is a fantastic choice. It's also a cost-effective way to enjoy these iconic snacks.If I had to find a downside, it's the potential for overindulgence, as these chips are seriously addictive. Moderation is key!In summary, the Pringles Potato Crisps Variety Pack is a snack lover's dream come true. It offers convenience, variety, and that irresistible Pringles taste. Whether you're stocking up for the office, the kids, or just yourself, this pack is a winning choice. Snack away and enjoy!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2023", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Jack Mawdsley", "rating": "4.0 ", "title": "Nice but arrived crushed", "content": "a lot of the cans content had been reduced to crumbs by the time of arrival.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 2, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Jackie Torres", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Great for meal prep or on the go", "content": "yummy, size perfect and easy", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Jinx", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Rat size/snack size", "content": "Our little inmates just love them. reviews: {"author": "Collin M.", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Great Fruit Snacks, Good Quantity, Good Price, Happy Parent", "content": "These are pretty good, and more importantly, tasty fruit snacks for the kiddo. What's extra nice about these is that they are made of actual fruit, without a ton of additional ingredients in them comparatively to other snacks out there. They actually taste good, and you get a decent size box for a good price. Respectable brand, with a good quality product that I don't feel bad for giving to my child, haha. Great amount as well so you can easily leave it on a shelf and not worry about running out for a bit.  Nice quick and easy snack for the kid when they are feeling a bit snacky. Would recommend!", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on March 13, 2024", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "LaHossBoss", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "*Update!* Still love and very sorry! Yummy! Just buy them already!", "content": "*Update to my Update*:I just must really be an idiot. I went through the entire box and it looks as though the rest of the packages are 5 oz. Now I am seriously questioning if the bag I had was from the box (I am 90% certain), but cannot absolutely prove it. I am returning my review to 5 stars for benefit of the doubt, that I am silly, and there really were 12 x 5oz packages in the box. I jumped to conclusions before going through the entire box and was just looking at the bag I had in my purse. I am almost certain that it came from the box because I have not pirchased any recently before or after rhis box. Honestly, even 11 x 5oz and 1 x 2.25oz packages are fine too for the price, albeit a bit shady or a simple accident, but I am fine with it wither way and overall. Sorry for the terrible rant below, please diregard. My original review below the update still stands.*Update*:Whoa! Wait a minute! I ordered a 12pk of *5oz* bags of Welch's Fruit Snacks! I actually received a 12 pk of *2.25oz* bags of Welch's Fruit Snacks. Now this I am *not* ok with! I made the purchase based on value. I could have bought these at the gas station for less at the full convenience markup! As sad as I am to say, and even though they were excellent, I will *not* be ordering again! I was duped. There are no returns. There is ZERO recourse to my issue. This is a serious problem. I understand no returns, maybe, but when the order is completely wrong on the Seller's end? I don't think that is legal. It is misrepresenting themselves and their products for sale! I only happened to notice this because I got to thinking that the bags seemed small and then going through the reviews SOMEONE ELSE mentioned the same thing happening! Once, ok....fix the fluke, but clearly this is ongoing! I am changing my 5 star review to 1 star until this is rectified or I am given half my money back for half the product I received!*I love Welch's fruit snacks...a lot! I like the larger sized bags because the little bags are too small for me and too much waste with all the little packets. I hate paying convenience markups at the grocery store, gas station, or at my workplace store, so thought I'd give it a try buying online. Not disappointed! They are fresh, soft, and tasty just like when I buy from the before mentioned places and cost much less! I can pack a bag for the day or throw in my bag for a snack at work and not have a bunch of tiny ones to carry around. I was wanting the large resealable bag, but honestly, the 2.25oz bags are great size-wise. I think the huge ones would be a lot to carry around. I can easily finish a 2.25oz bag and be done with it than to haul around a huge bag and hope they were completely sealed. I am sad that you can't subscribe to these and even the dash button makes you choose a seller. Small hassles, but I am rating the overall product and supplier. There was one that you could do this with (and was a couple bucks cheaper), but apparently became unavailable forever, and not just temporarily (or I would have just waited). Overall I am pleased with the purchase experience and quality of the product. The expiration date on the bulk box shows 6/2020 wich is a bit over 6 months away. I don't feel like that is too short an expiration because these will grow hard after too long and this is a good timeframe for maximum freshness and softness. I would think these had been manufactured recently based on the expiration date.", "date": "Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2020", "verified": "Verified Purchase"}; {"author": "Laura Alford", "rating": "5.0 ", "title": "Perfect Reward for my Students", "content": "This snack is perfect for my students!
